title: Mike Pence
added: On November 7, 2020, after several days of counting, Biden and Harris were declared by most major news networks to be the winners of the election.<ref>{{Cite web|title=Biden defeats Trump to win White House, NBC News projects|url=https://www.nbcnews.com/politics/2020-election/biden-defeats-trump-win-white-house-nbc-news-projects-n1246912|access-date=2020-11-08|website=NBC News|language=en}}</ref> Trump has refused to concede the election, and the Trump campaign has mounted legal challenges in several states, alleging electoral fraud brought on by the large number of mail-in ballots.<ref>{{Cite web|last=Fritze|first=Ledyard King and John|title=Trump attorney Rudy Giuliani says Trump won't concede, revives baseless claims of voter fraud|url=https://www.usatoday.com/story/news/politics/elections/2020/11/07/joe-biden-victory-president-trump-claims-election-far-over/6202892002/|access-date=2020-11-08|website=USA TODAY|language=en-US}}</ref> Pence has not commented publicly on the results.<ref>{{Cite web|last=Yashari|first=Leora|title=Meanwhile, Where In The World Is Mike Pence?|url=https://www.refinery29.com/en-us/2020/11/10155552/where-is-mike-pence-biden-win-election|access-date=2020-11-08|website=www.refinery29.com|language=en}}</ref>
